Step 1 | duration_ms=19342 | reasoning_tokens=707
  Thought: Answer: Step 1: Deprotonate acetylene (HC≡CH) with NaNH2, then alkylate with CC(C)CCBr to form the terminal alkyne HC≡CCH2CH2CH(CH3)CH3 (5-methyl-1-hexyne) | Step 2: Deprotonate this terminal alkyne again with NaNH2 to give the alkynide, then add cyclopentanone (O=C1CCCC1); aqueous workup affords the propargylic tertiary alcohol 1-(5-methylhex-1-ynyl)cyclopentan-1-ol | Step 3: Catalytically hydrogenate the alkyne completely (H2, Pd/C or Pt) to the alkane, giving OC1(CCCCC(C)C)CCCC1.

